cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.AR, cs.OS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses an approach for implementing lock-free data structures that can be used in parallel and concurrent environments. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the design of a software fallback path, which is related to programming language design. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another likely category as the paper discusses the implementation of lock-free trees. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of hardware transactional memory. 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the impact of the fallback path on performance, which is related to operating system design.
